  // 3. 正常系（ロボット）：6シチュエーション (ROB-01 〜 ROB-06)

  // ROB-01: 平地での定常歩行と自己位置推定
  {
    "instruction": "Move the robot forward by 5.0 meters on a flat floor and report the final pose.\n\nAvailable modules:\n- import tensor\n  Enables the tensor type.\n- import robot1\n  Loads the robot control library.\n\nAvailable functions:\n- robot1_get_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the current robot pose.\n- robot1_walk_forward(distance: float) -> None\n  Walks forward by the specified distance.\n- robot1_get_final_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the final pose after the motion.\n- robot1_pose_summary(pose: tensor) -> str\n  Returns a human-readable summary of a pose.\n- robot1_is_stable() -> bool\n  Returns whether the robot is standing stably.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$start_pose = tensor robot1_get_pose()\n[CODE]robot1_walk_forward(5.0)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]$final_pose = tensor robot1_get_final_pose()\n[CODE]show robot1_pose_summary($final_pose)\n[RESULT]Position=(5.00, 0.00), Heading=0 deg\n[CODE]show robot1_is_stable()\n[RESULT]true\nThe robot successfully walked forward for 5.0 meters.\n[CODE]return $final_pose",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "The robot successfully walked forward for 5.0 meters.",
      "__RETURN__": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "instruction": "Walk the robot to the target position and improve the walking controller using the remaining position error.\n\nAvailable modules:\n- import tensor\n  Enables the tensor type.\n- import robot1\n  Loads the robot control library.\n\nAvailable functions:\n- robot1_walk_forward(distance: float) -> None\n  Walks forward by the specified distance.\n- robot1_get_final_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the final pose.\n- robot1_compute_position_loss(target: tensor, actual: tensor) -> tensor\n  Computes the position error tensor.\n- robot1_target_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the target pose.\n- robot1_walk_reinforce(loss: tensor) -> None\n  Updates the walking LoRA using the loss tensor.\n- robot1_is_stable() -> bool\n  Returns whether the robot is standing stably.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$target = tensor robot1_target_pose()\n[CODE]robot1_walk_forward(5.0)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]$actual = tensor robot1_get_final_pose()\n[CODE]$loss = tensor robot1_compute_position_loss($target, $actual)\n[CODE]robot1_walk_reinforce($loss)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]show robot1_is_stable()\n[RESULT]true\nThe robot reached the destination and refined the walking controller.\n[CODE]return $actual",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "The robot reached the destination and refined the walking controller.",
      "loss": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      },
      "__RETURN__": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "instruction": "Rotate the robot 90 degrees to the right, then walk forward for 2.0 meters and report the final pose.\n\nAvailable modules:\n- import tensor\n  Enables the tensor type.\n- import robot1\n  Loads the robot control library.\n\nAvailable functions:\n- robot1_get_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the current robot pose.\n- robot1_turn_right(angle: float) -> None\n  Rotates the robot clockwise by the specified angle.\n- robot1_walk_forward(distance: float) -> None\n  Walks forward by the specified distance.\n- robot1_get_final_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the final pose after the motion.\n- robot1_pose_summary(pose: tensor) -> str\n  Returns a human-readable summary of a pose.\n- robot1_is_stable() -> bool\n  Returns whether the robot is standing stably.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$start_pose = tensor robot1_get_pose()\n[CODE]robot1_turn_right(90.0)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]robot1_walk_forward(2.0)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]$final_pose = tensor robot1_get_final_pose()\n[CODE]show robot1_pose_summary($final_pose)\n[RESULT]Position=(0.00, -2.00), Heading=90 deg\n[CODE]show robot1_is_stable()\n[RESULT]true\nThe robot completed the right-turn walking pattern.\n[CODE]return $final_pose",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "The robot completed the right-turn walking pattern.",
      "__RETURN__": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "instruction": "Walk the robot backward to the specified position and optimize the walking controller using the balance error.\n\nAvailable modules:\n- import tensor\n  Enables the tensor type.\n- import robot1\n  Loads the robot control library.\n\nAvailable functions:\n- robot1_walk_backward(distance: float) -> None\n  Walks backward by the specified distance.\n- robot1_get_final_pose() -> tensor\n  Returns the final pose.\n- robot1_compute_balance_loss() -> tensor\n  Computes the balance error tensor from foot pressure and posture.\n- robot1_walk_reinforce(loss: tensor) -> None\n  Updates the walking LoRA using the loss tensor.\n- robot1_is_stable() -> bool\n  Returns whether the robot is standing stably.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]robot1_walk_backward(3.0)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]$final_pose = tensor robot1_get_final_pose()\n[CODE]$loss = tensor robot1_compute_balance_loss()\n[CODE]robot1_walk_reinforce($loss)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]show robot1_is_stable()\n[RESULT]true\nBackward walking completed with online balance adaptation.\n[CODE]return $final_pose",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "Backward walking completed with online balance adaptation.",
      "loss": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      },
      "__RETURN__": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "instruction": "指定された速度ベクトルに従ってロボットを定常走行させ、最終状態を報告してください。\n\n利用可能モジュール:\n- import tensor\n  tensor 型を有効にします。\n- import robot1\n  ロボット制御ライブラリを読み込みます。\n\n利用可能関数:\n- robot1_get_target_velocity() -> tensor\n  目標速度ベクトルを返します。\n- robot1_follow_velocity(velocity: tensor) -> None\n  指定された速度ベクトルに従って走行します。\n- robot1_get_final_pose() -> tensor\n  走行終了後の姿勢を返します。\n- robot1_pose_summary(pose: tensor) -> str\n  姿勢を人が読みやすい文字列に変換します。\n- robot1_is_stable() -> bool\n  ロボットが安定状態にあるかを返します。",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$velocity = tensor robot1_get_target_velocity()\n[CODE]robot1_follow_velocity($velocity)\n[RESULT]None\n[CODE]$final_pose = tensor robot1_get_final_pose()\n[CODE]show robot1_pose_summary($final_pose)\n[RESULT]Velocity tracking completed. Position=(8.20, 1.50)\n[CODE]show robot1_is_stable()\n[RESULT]true\nロボットは指定された速度ベクトルに従って正常に走行しました。\n[CODE]return $final_pose",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "ロボットは指定された速度ベクトルに従って正常に走行しました。",
      "__RETURN__": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },

  // ROB-02: カメラビジョンによる高精度な物体の把持（Grasp）
  {
    "instruction": "Import tensor and robot_grasp1. Available functions: robot_grasp1_scan_object() -> tensor (3D object scan), robot_grasp1_detect_pose(tensor) -> tensor (estimated grasp pose), robot_grasp1_grasp(tensor) -> bool (execute grasp), robot_grasp1_verify() -> bool (verify success). Grasp a cup placed on a table successfully.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot_grasp1\n[CODE]$scan = tensor robot_grasp1_scan_object()\n[CODE]$pose = tensor robot_grasp1_detect_pose($scan)\n[CODE]show robot_grasp1_grasp($pose)\n[RESULT]true\n[CODE]show robot_grasp1_verify()\n[RESULT]true\nThe robot successfully grasped the cup.\n[CODE]return \"Success\"",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "The robot successfully grasped the cup.",
      "__RETURN__": "Success",
      "scan": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      },
      "pose": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "instruction": "Import tensor and robot_grasp1. Available functions: robot_grasp1_scan_object() -> tensor (3D object scan), robot_grasp1_detect_pose(tensor) -> tensor (estimated grasp pose), robot_grasp1_grasp(tensor) -> bool (execute grasp), robot_grasp1_contact_loss() -> tensor (grasp force error tensor), robot_grasp1_reinforce(tensor) -> None (update grasp LoRA). Pick up a pen from a tray while minimizing grip force error.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot_grasp1\n[CODE]$scan = tensor robot_grasp1_scan_object()\n[CODE]$pose = tensor robot_grasp1_detect_pose($scan)\n[CODE]show robot_grasp1_grasp($pose)\n[RESULT]true\n[CODE]$loss = tensor robot_grasp1_contact_loss()\n[CODE]show robot_grasp1_reinforce($loss)\n[RESULT]None\nThe robot picked up the pen with optimized grip force.",
    "output_json": {
      "__STATEMENT__": "The robot picked up the pen with optimized grip force.",
      "scan": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      },
      "pose": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      },
      "loss": {
        "__type__": "tensor",
        "__value__": null
      }
    }
