  // PHYS-08: 床面の摩擦変化（Slip/Low Traction）の検知とトルク制御
  {
    "instruction": "A robotic arm encountered an unexpected obstacle while inserting a component into an assembly fixture.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport assembly_cell\n  - assembly_cell_observe_insertion() -> tensor : Observe the insertion state.\n  - assembly_cell_insert_component() -> None : Insert the component.\n  - assembly_cell_estimate_contact_force() -> float : Estimate the contact force.\n  - assembly_cell_retract_tool(distance: float) -> None : Retract the tool.\n  - assembly_cell_compute_retry_pose() -> tensor : Compute a new insertion pose.\n  - assembly_cell_retry_insertion(pose: tensor) -> None : Retry the insertion.\n\nRecover without applying excessive insertion force.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import assembly_cell\n[CODE]$state = tensor assembly_cell_observe_insertion()\n[CODE]assembly_cell_insert_component()\n[EXCEPTION]InsertionException: The component contacted an unexpected obstruction.\n[COMMENT]Backing away is safer than forcing the insertion.\n[CODE]show assembly_cell_estimate_contact_force()\n[RESULT]18.6\n[CODE]assembly_cell_retract_tool(0.05)\n[CODE]$pose = tensor assembly_cell_compute_retry_pose()\n[CODE]assembly_cell_retry_insertion($pose)",
