    "instruction": "A mobile manipulator detected an abnormal force pattern while opening a heavy industrial valve.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport valve_operator\n  - measure_joint_state() -> tensor : Observe joint motion.\n  - rotate_valve() -> None : Attempt to rotate the valve.\n  - capture_force_profile() -> tensor : Acquire the measured force profile.\n  - infer_binding(force: tensor) -> dict : Infer the likely cause of resistance.\n  - release_torque() -> None : Reduce applied torque.\n  - adjust_grasp(offset: float) -> None : Reposition the end effector.\n  - retry_rotation() -> None : Retry the valve operation.\n\nAvoid increasing torque before understanding the resistance.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import valve_operator\n[CODE]$joint = tensor measure_joint_state()\n[CODE]rotate_valve()\n[EXCEPTION]ManipulatorException: Resistance increased unexpectedly during valve rotation.\n[COMMENT]Additional force should never be the first recovery strategy.\n[CODE]$force = tensor capture_force_profile()\n[CODE]show infer_binding($force)\n[RESULT]{\"offset\":0.018,\"cause\":\"misalignment\"}\n[CODE]$analysis = dict $RESULT\n[CODE]release_torque()\n[CODE]adjust_grasp($analysis.offset)\n[CODE]retry_rotation()",
