    "instruction": "An autonomous underwater robot experienced a sudden failure of its forward sonar while exploring a submerged tunnel.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport tunnel_explorer\n  - inspect_navigation_state() -> tensor : Observe the navigation state.\n  - explore_tunnel() -> None : Continue exploration.\n  - verify_backup_sensors() -> dict : Verify alternative sensing capabilities.\n  - retreat(distance: float) -> None : Move to a safer location.\n  - activate_backup_navigation() -> None : Enable redundant navigation.\n  - resume_exploration() -> None : Continue exploration.\n\nOnly continue the mission if redundant sensing is available.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import tunnel_explorer\n[CODE]$navigation = tensor inspect_navigation_state()\n[CODE]explore_tunnel()\n[EXCEPTION]SensorException: The forward sonar stopped providing valid range measurements.\n[COMMENT]Do not proceed into confined spaces without reliable obstacle perception.\n[CODE]show verify_backup_sensors()\n[RESULT]{\"available\":true,\"retreat\":2.5}\n[CODE]$backup = dict $RESULT\n[CODE]retreat($backup.retreat)\n[CODE]activate_backup_navigation()\n[CODE]resume_exploration()",
