  {
    "instruction": "An autonomous inspection robot lost communication with its remote supervisor while operating inside an underground utility tunnel.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport tunnel_inspector\n  - inspect_system_state() -> tensor : Observe the current system state.\n  - inspect_tunnel() -> None : Continue tunnel inspection.\n  - estimate_link_quality() -> dict : Evaluate communication quality.\n  - navigate_to_relay(point: str) -> None : Move toward a relay location.\n  - verify_connection() -> bool : Verify communication recovery.\n  - resume_inspection() -> None : Resume inspection.\n\nMaintain a recoverable communication path whenever possible.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import tunnel_inspector\n[CODE]$system = tensor inspect_system_state()\n[CODE]inspect_tunnel()\n[EXCEPTION]CommunicationException: Telemetry packets were no longer acknowledged by the control station.\n[COMMENT]Recovering communication takes priority over collecting additional inspection data.\n[CODE]show estimate_link_quality()\n[RESULT]{\"relay\":\"junction_4\",\"signal\":0.18}\n[CODE]$link = dict $RESULT\n[CODE]navigate_to_relay($link.relay)\n[CODE]show verify_connection()\n[RESULT]true\n[CODE]resume_inspection()",
