  {
    "instruction": "A warehouse sorting robot found that its barcode scanner produced inconsistent readings.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport sorting_unit\n  - capture_scan_frame() -> tensor : Capture scanner data.\n  - sort_package() -> None : Sort a package.\n  - extract_features() -> tensor : Extract barcode features.\n  - score_decoder(features: tensor) -> dict : Evaluate available decoding methods.\n  - switch_decoder(name: str) -> None : Activate another decoder.\n  - append_quality_log(report: dict) -> None : Record scanner quality information.\n\nChoose the most reliable decoding strategy instead of repeating failed scans.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import sorting_unit\n[CODE]$frame = tensor capture_scan_frame()\n[CODE]sort_package()\n[EXCEPTION]VisionException: Consecutive barcode reads produced conflicting identifiers.\n[COMMENT]Improving decoding reliability is preferable to repeatedly scanning the same label.\n[CODE]$features = tensor extract_features()\n[CODE]show score_decoder($features)\n[RESULT]{\"decoder\":\"adaptive\",\"confidence\":0.94}\n[CODE]$selection = dict $RESULT\n[CODE]switch_decoder($selection.decoder)\n[CODE]append_quality_log($selection)",
