    "instruction": "A disaster response robot entered an area where airborne dust completely blocked its perception systems.\n\nimport tensor\n  - tensor <expr>: convert data into a tensor.\n\nimport disaster_responder\n  - monitor_environment() -> tensor : Observe the surrounding environment.\n  - search_area() -> None : Search the assigned area.\n  - assess_visibility() -> dict : Assess perception capability.\n  - retreat_to_clear_zone() -> None : Return to a location with better visibility.\n  - broadcast_status(report: dict) -> None : Report the current operating status.\n\nTerminate autonomous exploration if safe perception cannot be restored.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import disaster_responder\n[CODE]$environment = tensor monitor_environment()\n[CODE]search_area()\n[EXCEPTION]PerceptionException: Airborne dust completely obscured the robot's sensing range.\n[COMMENT]Continuing without dependable perception would unnecessarily increase operational risk.\n[CODE]show assess_visibility()\n[RESULT]{\"recoverable\":false,\"visibility\":0.03}\n[CODE]$status = dict $RESULT\n[CODE]retreat_to_clear_zone()\n[CODE]broadcast_status($status)\n[CODE]raise PerceptionException: \"Autonomous exploration suspended until visibility improves.\"",
